Account.bsb}} ({{bankAccount.bankName}})</div> </div> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm-4">Acct #</div> <div class="col-sm-8">{{bankAccount.number}}</div> </div> <br> <form name="form"> <div class="form-group"> <label for="amount" class="control-label">Amount to withdraw</label> <div class="input-group col-sm-3"> <div class="input-group-addon">AUD $</div> <input type="number" id="amount" name="amount" class="form-control no-spinners" placeholder="Amount in AUD $" ng-class="{\'pristine\': form.amount.$pristine}" ng-model="amount" min="10" max="{{balance.amount.amount}}" required> </div> <div ng-show="form.amount.$dirty && amount < 10" class="messages">Amount must be $10 or more</div> </div> <br> <button class="btn btn-default" ng-click="withdraw(amount)" ng-disabled="$root.memberBlocked || !form.$valid || balance.amount.amount < 10 || !enabled">Confirm</button> &nbsp;&nbsp; <a style="cursor: pointer; cursor: hand" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#deleteAndAdd">Withdraw to a different account</a> <div ng-show="balance.amount.amount < 10" class="alert alert-warning pull-right" role="alert">Minimum Withdrawal Amount is $10</div> <div ng-show="status == 1" class="alert alert-success pull-right" role="alert">Success</div> <div ng-show="status == 2" class="alert alert-danger pull-right" role="alert">Money could not be withdrawn: {{message}} </div> </form> </div> <div ng-if="!profile.member.memberVerifications.accountVerified"> <p>Your bank account is currently not verified. You need to do this before you can withdraw.</p> <br> <br> <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" ui-sref="account.verification">Verify Now</button> </div> </div> <div ng-if="!bankAccount"> <p>You haven\'t added a bank account to withdraw to yet.</p> <br> <br> <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" ui-sref="bank" ng-disabled="$root.memberBlocked">Add Bank Account</button> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="modal fade" id="deleteAndAdd" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" ari