ing. </li> </ol> </li> <li class="strong"><strong>Enrolment</strong> <ol class="nested-numbering"> <li>To begin the enrolment process, a potential Affiliate shall submit a complete Program application via the Affiliate Website. </li> <li>Affiliate shall not attempt to open more than one Affiliate account without prior written consent from {{brandName}}, nor will Affiliate earn commissions on their own or related persons\' accounts. Affiliates are not permitted to wager with an Affiliate account. If you would like to wager with {{brandName}}, please set up a separate betting account. In the event of a violation, {{brandName}} has the right to void all current and future play as well as eliminate any earned commissions applicable from such play. </li> <li>{{brandName}} will evaluate the application and will notify the potential Affiliate of whether they are accepted to participate in the Program. {{brandName}} may reject any application if it is determined, in {{brandName}}s discretion, that the application or related website is unsuitable for the Program.</li> <li>Unsuitable websites include, but are not limited to, those that: <ol> <li>Infringe trademark rights of us or any third parties or otherwise violates the rights of any third party;</li> <li>Contain sexually explicit materials;</li> <li>Contain hate/violent/offensive content;</li> <li>Promote discrimination based on race, sex, religion, nationality, disability, sexual orientation, or age;</li> <li>Promote illegal activities or otherwise violate any applicable laws, including those targeting spyware, adware or SPAM;</li> <li>Violate any intellectual property rights, including, without limitation, scraping text or images from the Website;</li> <li>Are or contain pages that are targeted at any person under 18 years of age; Are otherwise considered by {{brandName}} to be offensive or inappropriate.</li> </ol> </li> <li> If {{brandName}} rejects the application, potential Affiliates may re-apply to the Program at any time. You should also note that if {{brandName}} accepts your application and your website is thereafter determined, at our discretion, to be unsuitable for the Program, we may terminate this Agreement.</li> </ol> </li> <li class="strong"><strong>Term and Termination</strong> <ol class="nested-numbering"> <li>The term of Affiliates participation in the Program ("Term") will begin upon {{brandName}}s written confirmation of your acceptance into the Program (which may include making payment to you in accordance with these Terms).</li> <li>Either {{brandName}} or Affiliate may terminate this Agreement and their participation in the Program at any time, with or without cause, by giving the other party at least 30 days written notice of termination (such notice to be sent to {{brandName}} by email to Rax@{{siteUri}}).</li> <li>Affiliate performance will be reviewed annually, based on the date of acceptance of your Program application.</li> <li>{{brandName}} has the right to suspend or terminate this Agreement immediately by notice in writing if: <ol> <li>Affiliate breaches any terms of this Agreement; or</li> <li>{{brandName}}, in its discretion, considers for any reason Affiliate is unsuitable to be an Affiliate</li> </ol> </li> <li>Where {{brandName}} exercises any power pursuant to clause 3.2 or 3.4, it shall not be required to disclose its reasoning in connection with any such suspension or termination. Where {{brandName}} discloses its reasons for such suspension or termination, it may withhold and/or terminate any payments that otherwise may have been due to Affiliate. For example, {{brandName}} will not pay Affiliate any amounts referrable to fraudulent (or suspected fraudulent) or banned Customers.</li> <li>Upon termination: <ol> <li>All rights and licenses granted to Affiliate shall terminate immediately.</li> <li>Affiliate must remove all {{brandName}} banners from their site and disable any links to the Website from their website.</li> <li>Subject to claus