                                                                            a.put("views/components/privacy-policy-content.html",'<h1>1. General</h1> <p>This is the privacy policy of {{companyName}} (ACN {{companyAcn}}) ({{brandName}}, {{siteUri}}, Our, We, Us). It sets out how {{brandName}} collects, uses, discloses and manages personal information. In carrying on business as an on-line wagering bookmaker, {{brandName}}, collects personal information about people who:</p> <ul> <li>apply to become or are {{brandName}} members,</li> <li>visit our website <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUri}}</a>, or use our mobile phone sites or tablet applications (together the website); </li> <li>send us queries or information;</li> <li>provide services to us or on our behalf; or</li> <li>apply to become or are our employees.</li> </ul> <p>provide services to us or on our behalf; or</p> <ul> <li>apply to become or are our employees.</li> </ul> <p>When collecting, using and handling personal information, {{brandName}} is required to comply with the <i>Privacy Act 1988</i> (Cth) (<strong>Privacy Act</strong>) and is bound by the Australian Privacy Principles (APPs) set out in the Privacy Act.</p> <p>{{brandName}} is committed to ensuring that the personal information it collects is collected, used, disclosed and protected in accordance with the Privacy Act and this Privacy Policy.</p> <p>In this Privacy Policy, \'personal information\' means information or an opinion about an identified individual, or an individual who is reasonably identifiable (whether the information is true or not, and whether it is recorded in any form or not).</p> <h1>2. Collection of Personal Information</h1> <p>The types of personal information we collect and how we collect it depends on the circumstances. If you apply to be, or are, a {{brandName}} member, we collect personal information about you:</p> <ul> <li>if you wish to subscribe to {{brandName}}s newsletter;</li> <li>to process your application for {{brandName}} membership;</li> <li>to provide member services to you;</li> <li>to identify you as a member for security purposes and to comply with our legal obligations;</li> <li>to maintain and manage your betting account;</li> <li>to upgrade and enhance your experience when using our website;</li> <li>to tailor or develop information, services or products which we think may suit your needs</li> <li>for marketing related purposes, including conducting research, conducting promotions, sending you newsletters and telling you (including via email, SMS or telephone) about products or services we think may be of interest to you); and </li> </ul> <p>The kinds of personal information that {{brandName}} generally needs to collect about {{brandName}} members and applicants for membership is:</p> <ul> <li>name</li> <li>residential address</li> <li>date of birth</li> <li>gender</li> <li>email address</li> <li>phone number(s)</li> <li>personally-submitted preferences</li> <li>bank account and credit card information</li> <li>financial information</li> <li>identity verification information</li> <li>recordings of all website activity and emails</li> </ul> <p>We will ordinarily collect your personal information directly from you, primarily through your use of the website or over the telephone. We may also collect personal information indirectly, for example through agents or affiliates we engage to undertake marketing activities.</p> <p>We are required by law to collect some personal information about people who use our services. We are required to collect certain information (including identity verification information) under the Anti-Money Laundering and Counter Terrorism Act 2006 (Cth).</p> <p>We may also collect personal information from job applicants, our employees and individuals associated with our business partners and service providers. Usually this information is limited to name and contact details and the other information we need for the purpose of managing the employment or business relationship.</p> <p>By accepting our terms and conditions upon registration You have given consent for {{siteUri}} to disclose your name, residential address and date of birth to a credit reporting agency and ask the credit reporting agency to provide an assessment of whether the personal information so provided matches (in whole or in part) personal information contained in a credit information file in the possession or control of the credit reporting agency to assist in verifying your identity for the purposes of the Anti-Money Laundering and Counter-Terrorism Act 2006. The credit reporting agency may prepare and provide {{siteUri}} with such an assessment and may use your personal information including the names, residential addresses and dates of birth contained in credit information files of you and other individuals for the purposes of preparing such an assessment.</p> <h1>3. Notification and Collection of Personal Information</h1> <p>When we collect personal information about you, we are required to take reasonable steps to ensure that you are aware of certain information relating to our collection, use, disclosure and handling of personal information. We generally do this by ensuring that a \'collection statement\' is provided when the personal information is collected.</p> <p>When you become a {{brandName}} Member, and in other situations where you provide personal information to us, we may deem your provision of personal information to be consent to {{brandName}} collecting, using and disclosing your personal information in accordance with the relevant collection statement.</p> <h1>4. Us and Disclosure of Personal Information</h1> <p>{{brandName}} only uses and discloses personal information for purposes that are related to the purposes for which we have collected the information. For {{brandName}} members and applicants for membership, this means we mainly use personal information for purposes connected with establishing and administering the membership and providing services and products related to on-line, as outlined wagering.</p> <p>{{brandName}} may use personal information to create aggregate data about {{brandName}} members through demographic profiling and statistical analysis of its database, in order to allow for more efficient operation of {{brandName}}s business. We may provide the information derived from such profiling or analysis in de-identified form to potential and existing stakeholders.</p> <p>{{brandName}} may disclose your personal information:</p> <ul> <li>to our agents and affiliates who undertake promotional and marketing activities on our behalf (including contacting you with special offers that may be of interest); </li> <li>to organisations that provide services (including IT, consultancy and advisory services) to us;</li> <li>to any particular third parties or classes of third parties that {{brandName}} notifies you at the time of collecting your personal information that your personal information may be disclosed to; </li> <li>for taking appropriate action if we have reason to suspect that unlawful activity or misconduct of a serious nature in relation to our services has been, is being or may be engaged in; </li> <li>to protect and maintain the integrity of particular sports / racing codes, by assisting controlling bodies in their inquiries or notifying such bodies of any betting activity {{brandName}} considers to be unusual or suspicious; </li> <li>where you have consented to the disclosure either expressly or by the circumstances and your conduct;</li> <li>where we consider disclosure is reasonably necessary to eliminate or minimise a risk to public health or safety, </li> <li>where we consider disclosure is reasonably necessary to investigate or deal with unlawful activity or serious misconduct; </li> <li>where we consider disclosure is reasonably necessary to locate missing persons;</li> <li>to establish or defend a legal claim; or where the disclosure is required or authorised by law.</li> </ul> <p>{{brandName}} will take all reasonable steps to ensure that any personal information which is disclosed to a third party is protected by that party in accordance with the Privacy Act and is used only for the purpose or purposes for which we supplied that information to them. Usually we do this by imposing contractual requirements on or seeking assurances from third parties as to their compliance with the Privacy Act.</p> <p>{{brandName}} does not disclose personal information to persons outside Australia.</p> <p>For information about {{brandName}}\'s use and disclosure of credit-related information, you should refer to {{brandName}}\'s Credit-related Information Policy (available at</p> <h1>6. Direct marketing and opting out</h1> <p>When registering as a {{brandName}} member, you may choose to receive promotional or marketing information from {{brandName}} by selecting the appropriate option on the registration page. If you do, from time to time we may use your personal information to inform you about {{brandName}}\'s products or services or about promotional activities, which {{brandName}} believes, may be of interest or of benefit to you. We may do this via email, SMS, telephone or mail.</p> <p>If you no longer wish to receive marketing or promotional material from {{brandName}} at all or in any particular form, you may contact us at any time by email to <a href="mailto:{{supportEmail}}">{{supportEmail}}</a> with your request with which we will comply as soon as is practical. Where we send you commercial electronic messages for direct marketing purposes, each message will contain a functional means for you to opt-out of receiving such messages.</p> <p>From time to time we may contact you in relation to the management and administration of your {{brandName}} account. These communications can be via any of the modes of contact recorded when registering as a Member. Such communication is not affected by your opt-in or opt-out status for direct marketing communications.</p> <h1>7. Personal information and our website</h1> <p>In using the website you agree to be bound by the terms of this Privacy Policy. {{brandName}} may review, change or update this Privacy Policy periodically and reserves the right to change the Privacy Policy at any time at its discretion by posting such changes on the website. We will publish our current Privacy Policy on the website and changes will take effect immediately at the time of publication. Your continued use of the website following publication will constitute your acceptance of those changes. You should review this Privacy Policy regularly and remain familiar with its terms.</p> <p>This Privacy Policy will not apply to other websites which are linked to the website and over which {{brandName}} has no control. {{brandName}} is not responsible for, the use of, or the protection of information provided to, such websites.</p> <p>You acknowledge that no data transmission over the Internet is totally secure. Accordingly, {{brandName}} does not warrant the security of any information, which you transmit to it. Any information that you transmit to {{brandName}} is transmitted at your own risk. You further acknowledge that Information posted on bulletin boards or communicated within a social media environment (for example, Facebook, Twitter, Chat Rooms) becomes public information. {{brandName}} does not guarantee the security of this type of information.</p> <p>Personal information has the potential to be collected when you use our website through the use of cookies. Cookies are pieces of data stored by your web browser on your hard drive which contain information relating to your use of the website. When you access the website, cookies may record details relating to your use of the website, including what pages you view from the website. {{brandName}} uses cookies for the detection of fraud, statistical analysis, systems administration and internal management purposes only.</p> <p>We may use third parties to serve ads on our website. The advertisers may employ cookies and action tags (also known as single pixel gifs or web beacons) to measure advertising effectiveness. Any information that these third parties collect via cookies and action tags is completely anonymous.</p> <h1>8. Management and security of personal information</h1> <p>{{brandName}} will take all reasonable steps to ensure that the personal information, which it collects, uses or discloses, is correct and is stored in a secure environment that is accessed only by authorised persons.</p> <p>{{brandName}} will destroy or permanently de-identify personal information when it is no longer required for any purpose permitted under the APPs, including our legal or operational obligations. {{brandName}} holds personal information in electronic database owned and operated by {{brandName}}. Once {{brandName}} receives your transmission, {{brandName}} will take reasonable steps to protect your personal information from misuse, loss and unauthorised access, modification and disclosure including by using password protected systems and databases and Secure Socket Layer ("SSL") technology.</p> <p>{{brandName}}s employees, agents and contractors are required to maintain the confidentiality of members\' personal information.</p> <p>{{brandName}} takes reasonable measures to ensure that personal information which it collects is accurate, complete and current and also when it uses and discloses it, that it is relevant, having regard to the purpose for which it is being used or disclosed. We give you the opportunity to correct and update personal information at any time, and may contact you on a periodic basis to seek the most up-to-date information from you. We will correct your personal information if we are satisfied that it is accurate and needs to be corrected.</p> <h1>9. Personal information about children</h1> <p>Persons under the age of 18 (Children) cannot become {{brandName}} members and are excluded from access to our services. We will not accept their information for the purposes of opening a wagering account. It is however, ultimately the responsibility of parents or guardians to monitor their childrens Internet activities including where appropriate by using Internet screening software.</p> <p>You are responsible for the security of and access to the website. You must log out of your account when you have completed your time on the website, and should not disclose your username, password or any account information to any other person.</p> <h1>10. Access to and correction of personal information</h1> <p>You may access personal information about you held by {{brandName}} by following the My Account link on the website or by contacting us at <a href="mailto:{{supportEmail}}">{{supportEmail}}</a>. To do so, you will need to provide evidence to confirm your identity before we can provide access. We will generally respond to all requests for access within 30 days of the request. If your request is particularly complex, or requires detailed searching of our records, there may be a cost to you in order for us to provide the information.</p> <p>Details of your betting transactions, deposits and withdrawals can also be accessed via the "My Transactions" section of the Member Services section of the website.</p> <p>However, we may refuse a request for access in certain circumstances set out in the Privacy Act, including where:</p> <ul> <li>providing access would be unlawful;</li> <li>we are required or authorised to do so by or under an Australian law or court/ tribunal order; or</li> <li>where giving access would be likely to prejudice enforcement related activities by or on behalf of an enforcement body. </li> </ul> <p>If we refuse your request or cannot give you access in the manner you have requested, we will do what we can to meet your requirements by other means. If we refuse access to your personal information, we will advise you in writing of the refusal, the reasons for the refusal, and the complaint mechanisms available to you.</p> <p>If you believe that the personal information {{brandName}} holds about you is inaccurate, incomplete or not current, please let us know and we will investigate and correct any inaccuracies if we are satisfied that a correction is required. Your personal information can be updated or corrected by you in the "Account Details" section of the website at any time after you log in. If there are any details you wish to update which you cannot please contact {{supportEmail}}</p> <h1>11. Complaints and further information</h1> <p>If you believe your privacy has been interfered with and wish to make a complaint, please contact our Compliance Manager. The Compliance Manager will investigate your complaint and notify you of the outcome. If your complaint indicates that there has been an interference with your privacy by a person other than {{brandName}}, the Compliance Manager may discuss your complaint with that other person in an attempt to resolve it.</p> <p>If you are not satisfied with the outcome of your complaint or the way we handle it, you may make a complaint to the Office of the Australian Information Commissioner at oaic.gov.au/privacy/making-a-privacy-complaint.</p> <p>If you have any queries, requests for access or correction or further information on our Privacy Policy, or if you have any concern about the handling of your personal information or wish to make a complaint, please contact {{supportEmail}}.</p> <p>Further Information about privacy concerns or complaints in Australia can be found on the Office of the Australian Privacy Commissioner\'s website at <a href="http://www.oaic.gov.au">www.oaic.gov.au</a>.</p>'),a.put("views/components/privacy-policy-modal.html",'<div class="modal-header"> <button type="button" class="close" ng-click="$dismiss()" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button> <h4 class="modal-title">Privacy Policy</h4> </div> <div class="modal-body"> <div ng-include="\'views/components/privacy-policy-content.html\'"></div> </div>'),a.put("views/components/rules-a-league-modal.html",'<div class="modal-header"> <button type="button" class="close" ng-click="dismiss()" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button> <h4 class="modal-title">Rules &amp; Scoring A-League</h4> </div> <div class="modal-body"> <tabset> <tab heading="Rule &amp; Scoring"> <h2>Point Scoring</h2> <p> <ul class="point-scoring"> <li>Minutes Played <span class="points">0.02 pts</span></li> <li>Goal <span class="points">7 pts</span></li> <li>Total Goal Assists <span class="points">4 pts</span></li> <li>Penalty Missed <span class="points">-6 pts</span></li> <li>Shot on Goal <span class="points">2 pts</span></li> <li>Crosses <span class="points">1 pt</span></li> <li>Fouls Drawn <span class="points">1 pt</span></li> <li>Red Card <span class="points">-2 pts</span></li> <li>Yellow Card <span class="points">-1 pts</span></li> <li>Passes Intercepted <span class="points">0.05 pts</span></li> <li>Passes Complete <span class="points">0.05 pts</span></li> <li>Tackles Won <span class="points">0.5 pts</span></li> <li>Saves (GK) <span class="points">1.5 pts</span></li> <li>Goal Allowed (GK, DEF) <span class="points">-2 pts</span></li> <li>Clean Sheet* <span class="points">6 pts</span></li> <li>Penalty Kick Save (GK) <span class="points">7 pts</span></li> <li>Single Goal Conceded* <span class="points">3 pts</span></li> </ul> * GK, DEF with 45 mins or more </p> <h2>Entering a Team</h2> <p> Each player is allocated a single position by {{brandName}}. Player positions are Forward, Midfielder, Defender and Goalkeeper. </p> <p> A contest participant is required to pick 2 Forwards, 3 Midfielders, 3 Defenders and 1 Goalkeeper. </p> <p> The total prices of each player selected must not exceed the relevant salary cap for that contest. </p> <p> A contest participant may make unlimited changes to their selected team line-up up until contest lockout. Lockout is in place from the commencement of the first match fixture of a contest. Players selected by a contest participant who do not take the field for any reason will score zero. </p> <h2>Live &amp; Final Scores</h2> <p> Live scoring for all {{brandName}} contests entered are available in the Live section of {{siteUri}}. Player scores are updated quarterly with a final score update approximately 2 hours after the completion of a contest. </p> <p> {{brandName}} uses Opta, the official statistics partner of the EPL, for all EPL statistics. Any changes to the official player statistics or perceived errors after the point scores are made final will not be taken into account and claims that a contest participants entry has been affected will not be considered. </p> <h2>Prize Allocation &amp; Payouts</h2> <p> The total prize pool comprises the aggregate value of all entry fees from contest entries less the {{brandName}} rake. </p> <p> Prizes are allocated as per the prize conditions set out each contest. For a detailed breakdown on Prize Payouts for this contest see the Prizes tab. </p> <p> These Rules and Scoring details form part of and are to be read in conjunction with the {{brandName}} <a href ng-click="openModal(\'terms-and-conditions\')">Terms and Conditions</a>. </p> </tab> <tab heading="Prizes"> <h2>Prizes<small>&#42;</small></h2> <table> <thead> <tr> <th>Place <th>Amount   <tbody> <tr ng-repeat="prize in prizes"> <td> <span ng-show="prize.placeRange.from === prize.placeRange.to">{{prize.placeRange.from | ordinal}}</span> <span ng-hide="prize.placeRange.from === prize.placeRange.to">{{prize.placeRange.from | ordinal}} - {{prize.placeRange.to | ordinal}}</span>  <td ng-if="!scale"> {{prize.amount.amount | money: prize.amount.currency}}  <td ng-if="scale"> {{doScale(prize.amount, contest.size, contest.entriesTotal).amount | money: prize.amount.currency}}    </table> <p ng-show="!scale" class="small top4">&#42; Contests will proceed if entries reach 50% of the contest size. This excludes Head to Head contests, which requires both members to enter for contest to proceed. Once the contest starts, the revised prize allocation is available within the contest live view..</p> </tab> </tabset> </div> '),a.put("views/components/rules-afl-modal.html",'<div class="modal-header"> <button type="button" class="close" ng-click="dismiss()" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button> <h4 class="modal-title">Rules & Scoring AFL</h4> </div> <div class="modal-body"> <tabset> <tab heading="Rule &amp; Scoring"> <h2>Point Scoring</h2> <p> <ul class="point-scoring"> <li>Goal <span class="points">6 pts</span></li> <li>Behind <span class="points">1 pt</span></li> <li>Kick <span class="points">3 pts</span></li> <li>Handball <span class="points">2 pts</span></li> <li>Mark <span class="points">4 pts</span></li> <li>Tackle <span class="points">4 pts</span></li> <li>Clanger Handball<span class="points">-3 pts</span></li> <li>Clanger Kick<span class="points">-3 pts</span></li> <li>Free Kicks For <span class="points">3 pts</span></li> <li>Free Kicks Against <span class="points">-3 pts</span></li> <li>Hitout <span class="points">1 pt</span></li> </ul> </p> <h2>Entering a Team</h2> <p> Each player is allocated a single position by {{brandName}}. Player positions are Forward, Ruck, Midfielder or Defender. </p> <p> A contest participant is required to pick 2 Forwards, 1 Ruck, 4 Midfielders and 2 Defenders </p> <p> The total prices of each player selected must not exceed the relevant salary cap for that contest. </p> <p> A contest participant may make unlimited changes to their selected team line-up up until contest lockout. Lockout is in place from the commencement of the first match fixture of a contest. Players selected by a contest participant who do not take the field for any reason will score zero. </p> <h2>Live & Final Scores</h2> <p> Live scoring for all {{brandName}} contests entered are available in the Live section of {{siteUri}}. Player scores are updated quarterly with a final score update approximately 2 hours after the completion of a contest. </p> <p> {{brandName}} uses Champion Data, the official statistics partner of the AFL, for all AFL statistics. Any changes to the official player statistics or perceived errors after the point scores are made final will not be taken into account and claims that a contest participants entry has been affected will not be considered. </p> <h2>Prize Allocation & Payouts</h2> <p> The total prize pool comprises the aggregate value of all entry fees from contest entries less the {{brandName}} rake. </p> <p> Prizes are allocated as per the prize conditions set out each contest. For a detailed breakdown on Prize Payouts for this contest see the Prizes tab. </p> <p> These Rules and Scoring details form part of and are to be read in conjunction with the {{brandName}} <a href ng-click="openModal(\'terms-and-conditions\')">Terms and Conditions</a>. </p> </tab> <tab heading="Prizes"> <h2>Prizes<small>&#42;</small></h2> <table> <thead> <tr> <th>Place <th>Amount   <tbody> <tr ng-repeat="prize in prizes"> <td> <span ng-show="prize.placeRange.from === prize.placeRange.to">{{prize.placeRange.from | ordinal}}</span> <span ng-hide="prize.placeRange.from === prize.placeRange.to">{{prize.placeRange.from | ordinal}} - {{prize.placeRange.to | ordinal}}</span>  <td ng-if="!scale"> {{prize.amount.amount | money: prize.amount.currency}}  <td ng-if="scale"> {{doScale(prize.amount, contest.size, contest.entriesTotal).amount | money: prize.amount.currency}}    </table> <p ng-show="!scale" class="small top4">&#42; Contests will proceed if entries reach 50% of the contest size. This excludes Head to Head contests, which requires both members to enter for contest to proceed. Once the contest starts, the revised prize allocation is available within the contest live view.</p> </tab> </tabset> </div> '),a.put("views/components/rules-bigbash-modal.html",'<div class="modal-header"> <button type="button" class="close" ng-click="dismiss()" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button> <h4 class="modal-title">Rules & Scoring Big Bash</h4> </div> <div class="modal-body"> <tabset> <tab heading="Rule &amp; Scoring"> <h2>Point Scoring</h2> <p>Each Player selected by You scores points based on their real life performances in the relevant Big Bash competition match. Points are allocated as follows:</p> <p>The statistics used are those provided by Opta, the official stats provider for Cricket Australia.</p> <p>Points are allocated as per the below:</p> <div class="row" style="margin-top: 20px"> <ul class="col-md-6 point-scoring"> <li class="header">Batting</li> <li>Runs (Per Run Scored) <span class="points">0.5 pts</span></li> <li>Duck <span class="points">-5 pts</span></li> <li>Strike Rate&#42; 200.0+ <span class="points">10 pts</span></li> <li>Strike Rate 175.0 - 199.99 <span class="points">8 pts</span></li> <li>Strike Rate 150.0 - 174.99 <span class="points">4 pts</span></li> <li>Strike Rate 125.0 - 149.99 <span class="points">2 pts</span></li> <li>Strike Rate 75.01 - 99.99 <span class="points">-5 pts</span></li> <li>Strike Rate 0.0 - 75.00 <span class="points">-10 pts</span></li> <li>&nbsp;</li> <li class="header">Batting Bonus</li> <li>50 Runs <span class="points">5 pts</span></li> <li>75 Runs <span class="points">7.5 pts</span></li> <li>100 Runs <span class="points">10 pts</span></li> </ul> <ul class="col-md-6 point-scoring"> <li class="header">Bowling</li> <li>Wicket <span class="points">10 pts</span></li> <li>Dot Balls <span class="points">0.5 pts</span></li> <li>Economy Rate 5.00 or less&#42;&#42; <span class="points">10 pts</span></li> <li>Economy Rate 5.01 - 6.00 <span class="points">8 pts</span></li> <li>Economy Rate 6.01 - 7.00 <span class="points">6 pts</span></li> <li>Economy Rate 7.01 - 8.00 <span class="points">4 pts</span></li> <li>Economy Rate 9.01 - 10.00 <span class="points">-4 p