ing agency to provide an assessment of whether the personal information so provided matches (in whole or in part) personal information contained in a credit information file in the possession or control of the credit reporting agency to assist in verifying your identity for the purposes of the Anti-Money Laundering and Counter-Terrorism Act 2006. The credit reporting agency may prepare and provide {{siteUri}} with such an assessment and may use your personal information including the names, residential addresses and dates of birth contained in credit information files of you and other individuals for the purposes of preparing such an assessment.</p> <h2>Security</h2> <p>Access to Your Account and to add to, delete or modify content on Your Account is password protected. You must memorise Your password or store Your password in a safe and secure place. You agree that You will not disclose Your password to anyone or allow any other person to access or use Your Account.</p> <p>You should check the My Transactions of your {{brandName}} account often to ensure there has been no unauthorised use of your account. If you suspect any unauthorised you must change your password immediately and contact <a href="mailto:{{supportEmail}}">{{supportEmail}}</a></p> <h1>3. Deposits, Withdrawals and Member Account Funds</h1> <p>All deposits made to {{siteUri}} are immediately available in the Members {{brandName}} Account, and can be accessed for placing bets (entering contests).</p> <p>If you are using a credit card your bank may charge you cash advance fee. {{brandName}} will not cover these costs.</p> <p>{{brandName}} will process all withdrawal requests immediately, with funds arriving in your nominated bank account the next working day. This may on occasion take up to 3 working days. In order to request a withdrawal You must first complete {{brandName}}s Identity Verification, Credit Card Verification and Bank Account Verification processes.</p> <p>{{siteUri}} holds Member Account Funds separately to operating cash and revenue. Member Account Funds are held within accounts at the National Australia Bank.</p> <h1>4. Restrictions on use of Our Websites</h1> <p>In accessing or using Our Websites you agree that you will not:</p> <ol> <li>use any automated device, software, process or means to access, retrieve, scrape, or index Our Websites or any content on Our Websites without Our express prior written consent; </li> <li>use any device, software, process or means to interfere or attempt to interfere with the proper working of Our Websites; </li> <li>undertake any action that will impose a burden or make excessive traffic demands on Our infrastructure that we deem, in Our sole discretion to be unreasonable or disproportionate site usage; </li> <li>use or index any content or data on Our Websites for purposes of competing with Us in any manner that we have not specifically authorised; </li> <li>transmit spam, chain letters, contests, junk email, surveys, or other mass messaging, whether commercial in nature or not; </li> <li>use Our Websites or any content from Our Websites in any manner which is, in Our sole discretion, not reasonable and / or not for the purpose it is made available; </li> <li>violate the rights of any person, including copyright, trade secret, privacy right, or any other intellectual property or proprietary right; </li> <li>pose as any person or entity or attempt to solicit money, passwords or personal information from any person; act in violation of any Term or condition of use of Our Websites </li> <li>reproduce, republish, retransmit, modify, adapt, distribute, translate, create derivative works or adaptations of, publicly display, sell, trade, or in any way exploit Our Websites or any content on Our Websites, except as expressly authorised by us; or </li> <li>transmit or attempt to transmit any computer viruses, worms, defects, Trojan horses or other items of a destructive nature. </li> </ol> <p>We reserve the right to exercise whatever means we deem necessary to prevent unauthorised access to or use of Our Websites, including, but not limited to, instituting technological barriers, or reporting your conduct to any person or entity.</p> <h1>5. Intellectual property</h1> <p>Unless indicated otherwise, all intellectual property in Our Websites is owned or licensed by Us. Subject to these Terms, You agree that You will not infringe Our intellectual property as contained in Our Websites and will not modify, copy, republish, frame, distribute or communicate any part of Our Websites or any information contained in it or otherwise use Our Websites in a way which will infringe Our intellectual property or other rights.</p> <h1>6. Use of Information</h1> <p>You agree that content You provide to Us in the course of accessing or using Our Websites, will be available to Us to use in any manner We think fit subject to applicable provisions of any legislation including, without limitation, privacy legislation.</p> <p>You agree, and continuously represent and warrant each time You access Your Account and Our Websites that You will not upload or otherwise provide any content which:</p> <ol> <li>is inaccurate, misleading, deceptive, incomplete, defamatory, fraudulent, unlawful, tortious or confidential;</li> <li>infringes the intellectual or other proprietary interests of third parties;</li> <li>contains spam, computer viruses, computer code, files or programs or other harmful components that are designed to interrupt, destroy, change or limit the functionality of Our Websites or any other computer software, hardware or other electronic equipment, information which in any way impinges on another user\'s use or enjoyment of Our Websites or otherwise breaches or encourages other users to breach these Terms; </li> <li>violates any law, statute or regulation; and/or</li> <li>forges information to disguise the origin of any Content.</li> </ol> <h1>7. Third Party Content</h1> <p>Our Websites contain content provided to Us by other parties (Third Party Content). This includes the information relating to sport, fantasy sport, player news and player stats. We are not responsible for, do not endorse and make no representations either expressly or impliedly concerning Third Party Content. Third Party Content does not represent Our views. You rely on Third Party Content completely at Your own risk.</p> <h1>8. Privacy</h1> <p>You agree to comply with Our privacy policy, guidelines and statements as may be applicable from time to time, which are incorporated into these Terms, and can be found at <a ui-sref="privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a>.</p> <h1>9. Self-Exclusion</h1> <p>You agree that you will not access any other {{siteUri}} account to use any of our services or products from which you have self-excluded, during the period of any such self-exclusion.</p> <p>To commence a self-exclusion period, you must:</p> <div class="well"> <p>Email <a href="mailto:{{supportEmail}}?Subject=Self Exclusion Request">{{supportEmail}}</a> with your account details and the desired period of your self-exclusion;</p> <p>Once request made has been verified under you will be blocked from logging into the website with your {{siteUri}} account for the period nominated and an email will be sent to you confirming your self-exclusion. The self-exclusion period cannot be cancelled until 7 days has elapsed. {{siteUri}} reserves the right to both extend self-exclusion and deny a request to cancel self-exclusion.</p> <p>You must not access or attempt to access your {{siteUri}} account or any {{siteUri}} account while you have been Self Excluded. It is your responsibility to ensure your account is secure from manipulation to access via multiple devices or any other means possible to access your {{siteUri}} account during your term of Self Exclusion.</p> </div> <h1>10. General Contest (Betting) Details</h1> <p>On the website You can select a team of NRL or AFL Players who score points based on their real life performance in matches in the AFL and NRL Football Competitions.</p> <p>Once You have selected a team for a contest, each contest entrant selects a contest entry amount (bet amount) for which they would like to enter their team.</p> <p>Each team entered for a particular game with a particular contest entry amount (bet amount) competes against the other teams submitted for that particular game with that particular entry amount. Once points have been determined, the money in the pool for that particular contest for that particular wager (after deduction of a rake) is distributed to the winning contest entrants as per the prize structure detailed in the rules and scoring section of that particular contest.</p> <p>Multi-person leagues will proceed if entries reach 50% of the contest size. The total prize pool will adjust as per the number of actual entries in the contest. Once the contest starts, the revised prize allocation is available within the contest live view.</p> <h1>11. Abandoned &amp; Cancelled Fixtures</h1> <p>Where any of the fixtures within a contest are cancelled or abandoned without an official result all bets are considered void and the entry amounts are returned to the members. There is no prize/winnings payouts for these voided contests.</p> <h1>12. Rules and Scoring for NRL</h1> <h2>Point Scoring for NRL</h2> <p>Each Player selected by you scores points based on their real life performances in the relevant NRL competition match. Points are allocated as follows:</p> <div class="well"> <p>The statistics used are those provided by Prozone.</p> <p>For an NRL competition match which goes to extra time, the points scored by a Player will be determined based on their total statistics for the match, including extra time.</p> </div> <p>Points are allocated as per the below:</p> <div class="well"> <p>Try = 10 pts, Try Assist = 8 pts, Tackle = 0.5 pts, Missed Tackle = -0.5pts, Tackle Break = 1pt, Offload = 2pts, Line Break = 6pts, Line Break Assist = 5pts, Run Metres Gained = 0.1pts, Error = -1pt, Goal Kick = 2pts, Missed Goal Kick = -1, Field Goal = 4, 40/20s = 4</p> </div> <h2>Entering an NRL Contest (placing an NRL Bet)</h2> <p>Each player is allocated a single position by {{brandName}}. Player positions are Hooker, Forward, Half/Five-Eighth, Outside Bac</p> <p>If entering an NRL contest You are required to pick 1 Hooker, 4 Forwards, 1 Half/Five-Eighth, 3 Outside Backs</p> <p>The forward (FWD) category includes both front rowers and back rowers.</p> <p>The outside back (OB) category includes all centers, wingers and fullbacks.</p> <p>The total prices of each player selected must not exceed the relevant salary cap for that contest.</p> <p>You may make unlimited changes to their selected team line-up up until contest lockout. Lockout is in place from the commencement of the first match fixture of a contest. Players selected by You who do not take the field for any reason will score zero.</p> <h1>13. Rules and Scoring AFL</h1> <h2>Point Scoring for AFL</h2> <p>Each Player selected by You scores points based on their real life performances in the relevant AFL competition match. Points are allocated as follows:</p> <div class="well"> <p>The statistics used are those provided by Champion Data, the official stats provider of the AFL.</p> <p>For an AFL football competition match which goes to extra time, the points scored by a Player will be determined based on their total statistics for the match, including extra time.</p> </div> <p>Points are allocated as per the below:</p> <div class="well"> <p>Goal = 6pts, Behind = 1pt, Kick = 3pts, Handball = 2pts, Mark = 4pts, Tackle = 4pts, Clanger Handball = -3, Clanger Kick = -3, Free Kick For = 3pts, Free Kick Against = -3pts, Hitout = 1pt</p> </div> <h2>Entering an AFL Contest (placing and AFL Bet)</h2> <p>Each player is allocated a single position by {{brandName}}. Player positions are Forward, Ruck, Midfielder or Defender.</p> <p>If entering an AFL contest You are required to pick 2 Forwards, 1 Ruck, 4 Midfielders and 2 Defenders.</p> <p>The total prices of each player selected must not exceed the relevant salary cap for that contest.</p> <p>You may make unlimited changes to their selected team line-up up until contest lockout. Lockout is in place from the commencement of the first match fixture of a contest. Players selected by You who do not take the field for any reason will score zero.</p> <h1>14. Rules and Scoring Football (EPL &amp; A-League)</h1> <h2>Point Scoring for Football (EPL &amp; A-League)</h2> <p>Each Player selected by You scores points based on their real life performances in the relevant football competition match. Points are allocated as follows:</p> <p>The statistics used are those provided by Opta, the official stats provider of the EPL and A-League.</p> <p>Points are allocated as per the below:</p> <div class="row" style="margin-top: 20px"> <ul class="col-md-6 point-scoring"> <li>Goal <span class="points">7 pts</span></li> <li>Goal Assists <span class="points">4 pts</span></li> <li>Minutes Played <span class="points">0.02 pts</span> (up to 90 minutes)</li> <li>Penalty Missed <span class="points">-6 pts</span></li> <li>Shot on Goal <span class="points">2 pts</span></li> <li>Crosses <span class="points">1 pt</span> (not including corners)</li> <li>Fouls Drawn <span class="points">1 pt</span></li> <li>Straight Red Card <span class="points">-2 pts</span></li> <li>Yellow Card <span class="points">-1 pt</span></li> <li>Passes Intercepted <span class="points">0.05 pts</span></li> <li>Passes Complete <span class="points">0.05 pts</span></li> <li>Tackles Won <span class="points">0.5 pts</span></li> <li>Saves (Goalkeeper Only) <span class="points">1.5 pts</span></li> <li>Goal Allowed (Goalkeeper and Defender Only) <span class="points">-2 pts</span></li> <li>Clean Sheet (Goalkeeper and Defender Only) if 45 mins or more played <span class="points">6 pts</span></li> <li>Penalty Kick Save (Goalkeeper Only) <span class="points">7 pts</span></li> <li>Single Goal Conceded (Goalkeeper and Defender Only) if 45 mins or more played <span class="points">3 pts</span></li> </ul> </div> <p>** Points not awarded for Penalty Shootout</p> <h2>Entering a Football Contest (placing an EPL or A-League bet)</h2> <p>Each player is allocated a single position by {{brandName}}. Player positions are Forward, Midfielder, Defender and Goalkeeper</p> <p>If entering a football contest You are required to pick 2 Forwards, 3 Midfielders, 3 Defenders and 1 Goalkeeper</p> <p>The total prices of each player selected must not exceed the relevant salary cap for that contest.</p> <p>You may make unlimited changes to their selected team line-up up until contest lockout. Lockout is in place from the commencement of the first match fixture of a contest. Players selected by You who do not take the field for any reason will score zero.</p> <h1>15. Rules and Scoring NFL</h1> <h2>Point Scoring for NFL</h2> <p>Each Player selected by You scores points based on their real life performances in the relevant NFL competition match. Points are allocated as follows:</p> <p>The statistics used are those provided by SportRadar, the official stats provider of the NFL.</p> <p>Points are allocated as per the below:</p> <h3>Offence</h3> <p>Rushing Yards = 0.1pts, Rushing Touchdown = 6pts, Passing Yard = 0.04pts, Passing Touchdowns = 4pts, Interceptions = -1pt, Receiving Yards = 0.1pt, Receiving Touchdown = 6pts, Receptions = 0.5pts, Kick Return Touchdown = 6pts, Punt Return Touchdown = 6pts, Fumbles Lost = -2, Own Fumbles Recovered Touchdown = 6pts, Two Point Conversions Scored = 2pts, Two Point Conversion Passes = 2pts, Field Goals = 3pts, Extra Point Conversions = 1pt</p> <h3>Defence</h3> <p>Sacks = 1pt, Opponent Fumble Recovered = 2pts, Interception Return Touchdown = 6pts, Fumble Return Touchdown = 6pts, Blocked Punt &amp; FG Return Touchdown = 6pts, Extra Points Return = 2pts, Kick-Off Return Touchdowns = 6pts, Punt Return Touchdowns = 6pts, Safeties = 2pts, Blocked Kicks = 2pts, Interceptions Made = 2pts, 0 Points Allowed = 10pts, 1-6 Points Allowed = 7pts, 7-13 Points Allowed = 4pts, 14-20 Points Allowed = 1pt, 28-34 Points Allowed = -1 Point, 35+ Points Allowed = -4pts</p> <h2>Entering an NFL Contest (placing an NFL Bet)</h2> <p>Each player is allocated a single position by {{brandName}}. Player positions are Forward, Midfielder, Defender and Goalkeeper</p> <p>If entering an NFL contest You are required to pick 1 Quarterback, 2 Running Backs, 3 Wide Receivers, 1 Tight End, 1 Kicker, 1 Defensive Team.</p> <p>The total prices of each player selected must not exceed the relevant salary cap for that contest.</p> <p>You may make unlimited changes to their selected team line-up up until contest lockout. Lockout is in place from the commencement of the first match fixture of a contest. Players selected by You who do not take the field for any reason will score zero.</p> <h1>16. Rules and Scoring NBA</h1> <h2>Point Scoring for NBA</h2> <p>Each Player selected by You scores points based on their real life performances in the relevant NBA competition match. Points are allocated as follows:</p> <p>The statistics used are those provided by SportRadar.</p> <p>Points are allocated as per the below:</p> <p>3 Point Field Goal 3 pts<br> 2 Point Field Goal 2 pts<br> Free Throw 1 pt<br> Rebound 1.2 pts<br> Assist 1.5 pts<br> Block 2 pts<br> Steal 2 pts<br> Turnover -1 pt</p> <h2>Entering an NBA Contest (placing an NBA Bet)</h2> <p>Each player is allocated a single position by {{brandName}}. Player positions are Point Guard, Shooting Guard, Small Forward, Power Forward and Center.</p> <p>If entering an NBA contest You are required to pick 2 Point Guards. 2 Shooting Guards. 2 Small Forwards, 2 Power Forwards and 1 Center.</p> <p>The total prices of each player selected must not exceed the relevant salary cap for that contest.</p> <p>You may make unlimited changes to their selected team line-up up until contest lockout. Lockout is in place from the commencement of the first match fixture of a contest. Players selected by You who do not take the field for any reason will score zero.</p> <p>Also for NFL, point 14 - please remove "Each player is allocated a single position by {{brandName}}. Player positions are Forward, Midfielder, Defender and Goalkeeper"</p> <h1>17. Rules and Scoring Big Bash / T20</h1> <p>Each Player selected by You scores points based on their real life performances in the relevant Big Bash / T20 competition match. Points are allocated as follows:</p> <p>The statistics used are those provided by Opta, the official stats provider for Cricket Australia.</p> <p>Points are allocated as per the below:</p> <div class="row" style="margin-top: 20px"> <ul class="col-md-6 point-scoring"> <li class="header">Batting</li> <li>Runs (Per Run Scored) <span class="points">0.5 pts</span></li> <li>Duck <span class="points">-5 pts</span></li> <li>Strike Rate&#42; 200.0+ <span class="points">10 pts</span></li> <li>Strike Rate 175.0 - 199.99 <span class="points">8 pts</span></li> <li>Strike Rate 150.0 - 174.99 <span class="points">4 pts</span></li> <li>Strike Rate 125.0 - 149.99 <span class="points">2 pts</span></li> <li>Strike Rate 75.01 - 99.99 <span class="points">-5 pts</span></li> <li>Strike Rate 0.0 - 75.00 <span class="points">-10 pts</span></li> <li>&nbsp;</li> <li class="header">Batting Bonus</li> <li>50 Runs <span class="points">5 pts</span></li> <li>75 Runs <span class="points">7.5 pts</span></li> <li>100 Runs <span class="points">10 pts</span></li> </ul> <ul class="col-md-6 point-scoring"> <li class="header">Bowling</li> <li>Wicket <span class="points">10 pts</span></li> <li>Dot Balls <span class="points">0.5 pts</span></li> <li>Economy Rate 5.00 or less&#42;&#42; <span class="points">10 pts</span></li> <li>Economy Rate 5.01 - 6.00 <span class="points">8 pts</span></li> <li>Economy Rate 6.01 - 7.00 <span class="points">6 pts</span></li> <li>Economy Rate 7.01 - 8.00 <span class="points">4 pts</span></li> <li>Economy Rate 9.01 - 10.00 <span class="points">-4 pts</span></li> <li>Economy Rate 10+ <span class="points">-8 pts</span></li> <li>&nbsp;</li> <li class="header">Bowling Bonus</li> <li>Maiden Over Bonus <span class="points">6 pts</span></li> <li>3 Wicket Haul <span class="points">5 pts</span></li> <li>4 Wicket Haul <span class="points">7.5 pts</span></li> <li>5 Wicket Haul <span class="points">10 pts</span></li> </ul> </div> <div class="row" style="margin-top: 20px"> <ul class="col-md-6 point-scoring"> <li class="header">Fielding</li> <li>Catch <span class="points">5 pts</span></li> <li>Wicketkeeper Catch <span class="points">4 pts</span></li> <li>Run Out <span class="points">5 pts</span></li> <li>Stumping <span class="points">7 pts</span></li> </ul> </div> <div class="row"> <p class="col-md-12">&#42; Strike Rate - Only batsmen scoring 20 runs or more<br> &#42;&#42; Economy rate - Must Bowl at least 2 overs</p> </div> <p> Each player is allocated a single position by {{brandName}}. Player positions are Batsman, Wicketkeeper, All Rounder, and Bowler. </p> <p> A contest participant is required to pick 3 Batsmen, 1 Wicketkeeper, 2 All Rounders, and 3 Bowlers. </p> <p>The total prices of each player selected must not exceed the relevant salary cap for that contest.</p> <p>You may make unlimited changes to their selected team line-up up until contest lockout. Lockout is in place from the commencement of the first match fixture of a contest. Players selected by You who do not take the field for any reason will score zero.</p> <h1>18. Rules and Scoring ODI</h1> <p>Each Player selected by You scores points based on their real life performances in the relevant ODI competition match. Points are allocated as follows:</p> <p>The statistics used are those provided by Opta, the official stats provider for Cricket Australia.</p> <p>Points are allocated as per the below:</p> <div class="row" style="margin-top: 20px"> <ul class="col-md-6 point-scoring"> <li class="header">Batting</li> <li>Runs (Per Run Scored) <span class="points">0.5 pts</span></li> <li>Duck <span class="points">-5 pts</span></li> <li>Strike Rate&#42; 125.0+ <span class="points">10 pts</span></li> <li>Strike Rate 110.01 - 124.99 <span class="points">8 pts</span></li> <li>Strike Rate 95.01 - 110.00 <span class="points">4 pts</span></li> <li>Strike Rate 70.01 - 85.00 <span class="points">-4 pts</span></li> <li>Strike Rate 0 - 70.00 <span class="points">-8 pts</span></li> <li>&nbsp;</li> <li class="header">Batting Bonus</li> <li>50 Runs <span class="points">5 pts</span></li> <li>75 Runs <span class="points">7.5 pts</span></li> <li>100 Runs <span class="points">10 pts</span></li> </ul> <ul class="col-md-6 point-scoring"> <li class="header">Bowling</li> <li>Wicket <span class="points">10 pts</span></li> <li>Dot Balls <span class="points">0.5 pts</span></li> <li>Economy Rate 3.50 or less&#42;&#42; <span class="points">10 pts</span></li> <li>Economy Rate 3.51 - 4.50 <span class="points">8 pts</span></li> <li>Economy Rate 4.51 - 5.00 <span class="points">4 pts</span></li> <li>Economy Rate 6.00 - 7.00 <span class="points">-4 pts</span></li> <li>Economy Rate 7.01 - 8.00 <span class="points">-6 pts</span></li> <li>Economy Rate 8.01+ <span class="points">-8 pts</span></li> <li>&nbsp;</li> <li class="header">Bowling Bonus</li> <li>Maiden Over Bonus <span class="points">3 pts</span></li> <li>3 Wicket Haul <span class="points">5 pts</span></li> <li>4 Wicket Haul <span class="points">7.5 pts</span></li> <li>5 Wicket Haul <span class="points">10 pts</span></li> </ul> </div> <div class="row" style="margin-top: 20px"> <ul class="col-md-6 point-scoring"> <li class="header">Fielding</li> <li>Catch <span class="points">5 pts</span></li> <li>Wicketkeeper Catch <span class="points">4 pts</span></li> <li>Run Out <span class="points">5 pts</span></li> <li>Stumping <span class="points">7 pts</span></li> </ul> </div> <div class="row"> <p class="col-md-12">&#42; Strike Rate - Only batsmen scoring 25 runs or more<br> &#42;&#42; Economy rate - Must Bowl at least 3 overs</p> </div> <p> Each player is allocated a single position by {{brandName}}. Player positions are Batsman, Wicketkeeper, All Rounder, and Bowler. </p> <p> A contest participant is required to pick 3 Batsmen, 1 Wicketkeeper, 2 All Rounders, and 3 Bowlers. </p> <p>The total prices of each player selected must not exceed the relevant salary cap for that contest.</p> <p>You may make unlimited changes to their selected team line-up up until contest lockout. Lockout is in place from the commencement of the first match fixture of a contest. Players selected by You who do not take the field for any reason will score zero.</p> <h1>19. Live &amp; Final Scores</h1> <p>Live scoring for all {{brandName}} contests entered are available in the Live section of {{siteUri}}. Player scores are updated quarterly with a final score update approximately 2 hours after the completion of a contest. {{brandName}} uses Champion Data for AFL statistics, Opta for EPL and RWC, and SportRadar for NFL and NBA and Prozone for NRL statistics. Any changes to the official player statistics or perceived errors after the point scores are made final will not be taken into account and claims that a contest participants entry has been affected will not be considered.</p> <h1>20. Prize Allocation &amp; Payouts</h1> <p>{{brandName}} uses Champion Data for AFL statistics, Opta for EPL and RWC, and SportRadar for NFL and NBA and Prozone for NRL statistics. Any changes to these statistics or perceived errors after the point scores are made final will not be taken into account and claims that a contest participants entry has been affected will not be considered.</p> <p>Prizes are allocated as per the prize conditions set out in each contest. For a detailed breakdown on Prize Payouts for a contest see the Prizes tab in the Rules, Scoring &amp; Prizes section of that contest.</p> <p>Multi-person leagues will proceed if entries reach 50% of the contest size. The total prize pool will adjust as per the number of actual entries in the contest. Once the contest starts, the revised prize allocation is available within the contest live view.</p> <p>One exception to this is large tournaments. Prize pool and contest are usually guaranteed for large tournaments regardless of how many members enter.</p> <p>Live scoring for all {{brandName}} contests entered are available in the Live section of {{siteUri}}. Player scores are updated quarterly with a final score update approximately 2 hours after the completion of a contest.</p> <p>{{brandName}} uses Champion Data for AFL statistics, Opta for EPL and RWC, and SportRadar for NFL and NBA and Prozone for NRL statistics. Any changes to these statistics or perceived errors after the point scores are made final will not be taken into account and claims that a contest participants entry has been affected will not be considered.</p> <p>In the case of two teams within a contest having a tied score, final payouts are calculated upon contest settlement.</p> <h1>21. Re-Sizing Contests</h1> <p>Moneyball reserves the right to re-size contests.</p> <p>For guaranteed contests, they will only be re-sized to allow for a larger prize pool with more participants with a rake % less than or equal to the original rake %.</p> <p>For non-guaranteed contests, they will only be re-sized to allow the contest to go ahead with 50% of the required entries in the contest. In this case the rake % will remain the same, with the new prize amount allocation reflected within the contest.</p> <h1>22. Tied Contest Entrant Scores</h1> <p>Where there are two or more winning entries (bets) on the same ranking, they share equally the prize payouts that would have applied to them had they been consecutively, and not equally, ranked.</p> <h1>23. Settlement of a Contest</h1> <p>Contest settlement will happen within 24 hours of the conclusion of the final real-game fixture of a contest.</p> <h1>24. Cancelled Matches</h1> <p>Where an actual real-life game fixture which forms part of a contest is cancelled all entries (bets) on any contest which involves that real-life game fixture will be cancelled and monies refunded to the relevant {{siteUri}} member accounts.</p> <h1>25. Uncontrollable Circumstances</h1> <p>If, for any reason, a contest is not capable of running as planned, including due to infection by computer virus, bugs, tampering, unauthorised intervention, fraud, technical failure or any other causes beyond the control of {{siteUri}}, which corrupt or affect the administration, security, integrity or proper conduct of a contest, {{siteUri}} reserves the right in its sole discretion to take any action that may be available, subject to any applicable laws, including cancelling all entries (bets) on the contest and refunding monies.</p> <h1>26. Management of Balances from Abandoned Accounts</h1> <p>{{siteUri}} shall consider an account abandoned after 5 consecutive years of no deposits, withdrawals or betting activity.</p> <p>Once an account is deemed Abandoned, should there be a credit balance {{brandName}} will attempt to contact the member through all available contact channels to organize withdrawal of the balance. Should all avenues be exhausted, {{siteUri}} will refer the matter to <a href="mailto:gaming@norfolk.net.nf">gaming@norfolk.net.nf</a> for a final decision regarding the credit balance.</p> <h1>27. Management of Balances from Frozen Accounts</h1> <p>Where and when permitted by Law, {{siteUri}} will contact members with Frozen {{brandName}} Accounts to organize withdrawal/return of any credit balance in their {{siteUri}} account.</p> <h1>28. Complaints and Dispute Resolution</h1> <p>Should You not be satisfied with a response from <a href="mailto:{{supportEmail}}">{{supportEmail}}</a> You can directly escalate to our management team by contacting <a href="mailto:{{complaintsEmail}}">{{complaintsEmail}}</a></p> <p>If any dispute or complaint cannot be settled satisfactorily between us and you, the matter shall be referred to a representative of the Norfolk Island Gaming Authority at <a href="mailto:gaming@norfolk.net.nf">gaming@norfolk.net.nf</a> for final determination. If the dispute or complaint concerned a bet, the bet will be adjusted in accordance with the decision of the Authority, whose decision is final and binding on both parties.</p> <p>You have the right to contact the Norfolk Island Gaming authority directly at <a href="mailto:gaming@norfolk.net.nf">gaming@norfolk.net.nf</a></p> <h1>29. Law and Jurisdiction</h1> <p>These Terms, and the agreement of which they form part, are governed by the laws of the Norfolk Island, an Independent Territory of Australia.</p> <h1>30. Limitation Of Liability</h1> <p>You agree that, to the maximum extent permitted by law, We are not liable to You or anyone else for any loss or damage (including, without limitation, any direct, indirect, special or consequential loss) arising as a result of breach of these Terms, in tort (including negligence) or otherwise arising out of, or in connection, with:</p> <ol> <li>the use of Our Websites;</li> <li>any Content You upload or otherwise provide;</li> <li>the use by Us of information provided by You to Us through Our Websites;</li> <li>being unable to access Our Websites for whatever reason and however arising, including (without limitation) negligence; </li> <li>the failure of Our Websites for whatever reason and however arising including (without limitation) negligence; and/or </li> <li>the use of Your password by You or any third party to whom You have made the password available.</li> </ol> <p>We expressly limit, and You agree, Our liability for breach of a condition or warranty implied or a consumer guarantee imposed by virtue of any legislation to the supply of the services again or the payment of the cost of having the services supplied again (the choice of which is to be at Our sole discretion).</p> <p>You indemnify Us against any action, liability, claim, loss, damage, proceeding, expense (including legal costs) suffered or incurred by Us, arising from, or which is directly or indirectly, related to:</p> <ol> <li>Your breach or non-observance of any of these Terms;</li> <li>any Content You upload or otherwise provide;</li> <li>any breach or inaccuracy in any representations or warranties made to Us; and/or</li> <li>any breach, or alleged breach, of intellectual or other proprietary rights or interests of third parties.</li> </ol> <p><strong>These terms were last updated on the 04/01/2016</strong></p>'),
