btn-sm">Create Contest </button> </div> </div> <div class="col-sm-8"> <div class="pull-right"> <span ng-show="!msg">{{selectedContests}} contest<span ng-show="selectedContests != 1">s</span> selected&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> <span ng-show="msg" class="label label-success">{{msg}}</span> <button ng-show="!msg" ng-click="invite()" class="btn btn-default btn-sm" ng-disabled="selectedContests < 1 || challenging">Share </button> <button type="button" class="btn btn-warning btn-sm" data-dismiss="modal" ng-click="msg = null;challenging = false"> <span ng-show="challenging">Close</span><span ng-show="!challenging">Cancel</span></button> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <script type="text/ng-template" id="contestDetails.html"><div contest-details contest="selectedContest" modal="modalInstance"></div></script> <script type="text/ng-template" id="inviteFriends.html"><div invite-friends contest="contest" modal="modalInstance" email="email"></div></script>'),
                                                                            a.put("views/gamble-responsibly.html",'<div class="title-bar"> <div class="container"> <h1 class="title">Gamble Responsibly</h1> </div> </div> <div class="container"> <div class="panel"> <div class="panel-body" ng-cloak> <h1>Overview</h1> <p>For the majority of people, gambling is an enjoyable leisure and entertainment activity. But for some, gambling can have negative impacts. As a result, we have developed this policy to communicate our approach to responsible gambling and minimising harm to consumers who may be vulnerable to problem gambling. Our betting operations are governed by this policy and a code of practice.</p> <h1>What is Responsible Gambling?</h1> <p>Responsible Gambling is a broad concept that aims to ensure gambling is conducted in a manner whereby the potential for harm associated with problem gambling is minimised.</p> <p>It respects the responsibility of individuals for their own actions, but also acknowledges a responsibility on the part of service providers.</p> <p>Responsible gambling has regard to the context in which gambling occurs, the inducements made to gamble, the way the gambling service operates and the integrity of the gambling operator.</p> <p>The aim is to enable persons to make informed decisions about their participation in gambling and, if harm has occurred, to access gambling help services.</p> <h2>What is Problem Gambling?</h2> <p>Problem gambling occurs where a vulnerable consumer lacks control over their gambling, particularly the scope and frequency of gambling, the amount of money gambled and the amount of time devoted to gambling. The negative consequences of problem gambling may include:</p> <ol> <li>the gambler suffering excessive financial losses relative to the gamblers means;</li> <li>adverse personal effects on the gambler and/or their family;</li> <li>adverse affects on employment and work performance; and</li> <li>other costs which are borne by the community.</li> </ol> <h1>Customer Care Principles and Responsible Gambling</h1> <p>We aim to consistently care for our customers and promote responsible gambling practices.</p> <p>For the vast majority of people, the attraction to test ones judgement or luck does not create problems. Gambling generally should be a pleasurable form of entertainment.</p> <p>The aim is to achieve a balanced approach in the provision of wagering services, taking account of the interests of our customers, the community at large and us as the wagering operator.</p> <h1>Responsible Gambling Policy</h1> <p>We are committed to sharing responsibility, with Governments and communities, for helping problem gamblers to identify their problem and seek assistance.</p> <p><strong>Some of the ways that we do this are:</strong></p> <ol> <li>allowing our customers to self-exclude (either temporarily or permanently) from betting with us;</li> <li>providing Responsible Gambling information and messages to our customers;</li> <li>training our staff about Responsible Gambling at induction and at least every 2 years; and</li> <li>referring our customers who are at risk of problem gambling to gambling-related support services.</li> </ol> <p><strong>We aim to achieve the following outcomes:</strong></p> <ol> <li>minimising the extent of gambling related harm to individuals and the broader community;</li> <li>enabling customers to make informed decisions about their gambling practices;</li> <li>enabling people adversely affected by gambling to have access to timely and appropriate assistance and information; </li> <p>promoting a shared understanding between individuals, communities, the gambling industry and Government of responsible gambling practices; and</p> <li>ensuring the gambling industry provides safe and supportive environments for the delivery of gambling products and services. </li> </ol> <h1>Minors</h1> <p>As a responsible operator, we are committed to maintaining our reputation by actively taking steps to exclude minors from placing a wager using our betting platforms. Our services are designed to appeal to, and be used by persons who are at least 18 years old.</p> <h1>Filtering Options</h1> <p>Certain filtering options can be enabled to prohibit underage persons from entering the online sports betting software, as the minimum legal age to gamble is 18 years. The comprehensive list of filtering options available for download can be accessed through these sites:</p> <ul> <li>http://www.cyberpatrol.com</li> <li>http://www.gamblock.com</li> <li>http://www.safekids.com</li> <li>http://www.surfcontrol.com</li> <li>http://www.solidoak.com</li> <li>http://www.netnanny.com</li> <li>http://www.betfilter.com</li> <li>http://www.rgmanager.com</li> </ul> <h1>Where to Get Help</h1> <p>You can call the Gambling Helpline on 1800 858 858 or visit:</p> <ul> <li><a href="http://www.gamblinghelponline.org.au/">Gambling Help Online</a></li> <li><a href="http://www.gamblinghelp.nsw.gov.au/">Gambling Help (New South Wales)</a></li> <li><a href="http://www.gamblersanonymous.org.au/">Gamblers Anonymous</a></li> </ul> <p>Or alternatively you can contact the Customer Service Manager through <a href="mailto:{{supportEmail}}">{{supportEmail}}</a> for other gambling support providers in your area.</p> <h2>Self-Exclusion</h2> <p>If you feel that you are losing control of your play and would like help in restricting your access to our betting platforms, we offer you the following options to set a voluntary self-exclusion period by contacting <a href="mailto:{{supportEmail}}">{{supportEmail}}</a> with the details of their account details and period of self-exclusion. Once the request has been verified, {{brandName}} will enforce a self-exclusion period immediately. {{brandName}} will not consider any requests to cancel this request within 7 days.</p> <p>Please note: If a player chooses to opt for a self-exclusion period, {{siteUri}} Management reserves the right to keep all accounts closed indefinitely.</p> <p>These terms were last updated on 22/02/2015</p> </div> </div> </div>'),a.put("views/help.html",'<div class="title-bar"> <div class="container"> <h1 class="title">Help</h1> </div> </div> <div class="container"> <div class="panel"> <div class="panel-body" ng-cloak> <p>The easiest way to get {{brandName}} help is to read our FAQs below.</p> <p>Cant find the answer you want? Email us at <a href="mailto:{{supportEmail}}">{{supportEmail}}</a></p> <h1>FAQ</h1> <h2>Basics</h2> <accordion> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> Can I access {{brandName}} from my smartphone or tablet? </accordion-heading> <p>Yes, {{brandName}} is mobile and tablet friendly when viewed in your mobile internet browser.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> What is {{brandName}}? </accordion-heading> <p>{{brandName}} is a daily and weekly fantasy sports platform, where members pay to play in contests against their friends and the wider {{brandName}} community. Members select their ultimate fantasy team for either a full weekend of games (eg, All of round), or just for one day (eg, Super Saturday).</p> <p>Members have a broad range of contest sizes to choose from, from 2 participants to 1000s of participants in size. </p> <p>Members also have a broad range of entry fees available, from $2 as the minimum entry fee upwards.</p> <p>Once the games have been played, the players accumulate their fantasy points scores , and the contest is complete, whoever picked the best performing combination of players , wins the prize pool.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> How do I play {{brandName}}? </accordion-heading> <p>{{brandName}} is played weekly and daily rather than season long. Refer to our <a ui-sref="how-it-works">how it works</a> section for full details on contest types, team selection, and prize allocation.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> Why should I play {{brandName}}? </accordion-heading> <p><strong>There is no season long commitment!</strong> At {{brandName}} we run new contests weekly, either across one round (eg, "All of round 4") or across a specific day (eg, "Super Saturday"). You can play as often as you want, whenever you want.</p> <p><strong>Win real cash prizes!</strong> You have multiple game types to select from. You can go head to head against other members and friends; you can create your own contests for 3 - 50 participants; or you can enter larger {{brandName}} contests of 50 to 1000s of participants. Its entirely up to how much you want to spend week to week and prizes you go after!</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> How are the prizes allocated? </accordion-heading> <h3>Head to head</h3> <p>Winner takes all</p> <h3>User created leagues (by participant size)</h3> <p>3  10: either the top 2 finishers, or winner takes all</p> <p>11  20: either top 3 finishers, or winner takes all</p> <p>21  30: either top 4 finishers, or winner takes all</p> <p>31  50: either top 5 finishers, or winner takes all</p> <h3>System created leagues</h3> <p>Prizes in system created leagues are allocated as per the prize conditions set out in each contest. For a detailed breakdown on Prize Payouts for a contest, see the Prizes tab in both the Rules, Scoring & Prizes section of that contest or in the pop-up window accessed by clicking the contest name in the lobby.</p> <p>If two or more finishers share the same ranking, they then share equally the distribution of prizes that would have been applied to them had they been consecutively ranked.</p> <!--<h3>50/50</h3>\n\n          <p>Half the field wins, half the field looses. For example, if 100 people have entered a $10 contest, $900 is\n            up for grabs. Finishers 1-50 will each receive $18, and finishers 51-100 get nothing.</p>--> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> How do I sign-up to {{brandName}}? </accordion-heading> <p><a ui-sref="signup.me">Create an account</a> and start playing</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> Ive forgotten my log in details? </accordion-heading> <p>Simply go to the {{brandName}} <a ui-sref="signin">sign in</a> page click the <a ui-sref="reset">forgot password</a> link and you will be sent a reminder.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> How do I delete my account? </accordion-heading> <p>Please email us at <a href="mailto:{{supportEmail}}">{{supportEmail}}</a></p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> Who can play {{brandName}}? </accordion-heading> <p>You must be 18+ years of age and a resident of Australia to play {{brandName}}.</p> <p>All registered members must verify their identity within 90 days of joining, in compliance with AUSTRACs AML/CTF regulations.</p> <p>You will also be required to verify any credit card you use to deposit funds, and also any bank account you want to withdraw to.</p> <p>For more information please see our <a ui-sref="terms-and-conditions">Terms and Conditions</a>.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> Is {{brandName}} licensed to operate a wagering platform? </accordion-heading> <p>{{companyName}} is licensed to operate wagering services within all Australian states and territories through the Norfolk Island Gaming Authority.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> Where can I see contests I have entered? </accordion-heading> <p>All contests you have entered that have not yet commenced can be viewed in <a ui-sref="upcoming">upcoming contests</a>.</p> <p>All contests underway can be viewed in <a ui-sref="live">live contests</a>.</p> <p>All completed contests can be viewed in <a ui-sref="history">contest history</a>.</p> <p>You can also see all transactions, including contests entered, prizes won, deposits made and withdrawals made, in your <a ui-sref="account.wallet">transaction details</a>.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> How do I edit my team? </accordion-heading> <p>For any contest you have entered, you have up until nearing the start of the first game for that contest to edit your team. You can do this through <a ui-sref="upcoming">upcoming contests</a>, select the contest in question and then edit your team.</p> <p>Once the contest is locked (ie, the first match for that contest is due to commence), then no further editing of your team can be done.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> When does a contest close for editing my line up? </accordion-heading> <p>Contests are locked down for editing a short period of time prior to the commencement of the first game of the contest. Once lockdown has occurred, no further edits can be made.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> How do I know who I am competing against in my contest? </accordion-heading> <p>All members who have entered a contest will be shown as a entries in that contest. This can be seen in the enter contest screens.</p> </accordion-group> </accordion> <h2>Verifying my Identity, Credit Cards, and Bank Account</h2> <accordion> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> Why do I need to do this? </accordion-heading> <p>{{brandName}} takes its commitments to ensuring your safety and ensuring safe contest participation seriously. Not only do we have obligations to verify your identity, we also want to ensure that any deposits made or withdrawals requested are genuine and above suspicion. This protects both {{brandName}} and our members.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> How do I verify my identity? </accordion-heading> <p>Please refer to the verification status page of your account on how you can verify your identity.</p> <p>We partner with GreenID, who when you join {{brandName}} will attempt to verify your identity based on the information you add in the sign up stage. If your identity cannot be verified at this stage, we will request further certified documentation to establish verification. Everything you need to know is on your <a ui-sref="account.verification">verification status</a> section of your account. </p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> How do I change my personal details? </accordion-heading> <p>Please contact <a href="mailto:{{supportEmail}}">{{supportEmail}}</a> to assist in changing your personal details.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> How do I verify my credit card? </accordion-heading> <p>Please refer to your verification status section of your account for more detail. You are required to upload a close up image of your credit card which clearly displays the name, card number, and expiry date of the credit card you have used for a deposit.</p> <p>If you have used more than one card for deposits, you will be required to verify each card.</p> <p>{{brandName}} enforces restrictions on deposits and withdrawals until such time credit card verification has taken place.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> Why do I need to verify my credit card? </accordion-heading> <p>{{brandName}} must verify that the member of an account is the owner of any credit card used to deposit funds. This is for your safety and ours.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> How do I verify my bank account? </accordion-heading> <p>Simply go to the bank account verification section on your verification status section of your account. You will be asked to add your account name, BSB, and account number, as well as verifying these details through the upload of a certified document, being your monthly bank statement for the account in question.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> Why do I need to verify my bank account? </accordion-heading> <p>Account verification is a requirement in order to withdraw funds from {{brandName}}.</p> </accordion-group> </accordion> <h2>Rules and Scoring</h2> <accordion> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> How are contest scores calculated? </accordion-heading> <p>For {{brandName}} scoring see the <strong>Rules and Scoring</strong> tab for your selected sport and contest.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> Where does {{brandName}} get its player performance data to base its scores on? </accordion-heading> <p>{{brandName}} sources its player performance data from Champion Data, Opta, SportRadar and Prozone. Champion Data, Opta, SportRadar and Prozone provide {{brandName}} with regular updates on the actions of players, which {{brandName}} then applies its scoring against. For example, Player X performs action Y which results in Z points. This is based on real life performances of these players in the context of the game they are playing in.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> The games are all over and I have won so why is \'My Account\' not showing my winnings? </accordion-heading> <p>We wait until all fantasy points have been reported to {{brandName}} from our data provider. This ensures all final box scores are accurate; however occasionally there can be some last minute changes due to our stat provider awarding fantasy points manually. Contests will be settled the following day if there is an issue with scoring or obtaining official results.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> How does the salary cap allocation work? </accordion-heading> <p>Players are given a virtual salary cap based on a combination of their season long performances (or previous season performances for the commencement of season), and their recent form.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> When is a contest result final? </accordion-heading> <p>{{brandName}} aims to finalise a contest and prize allocations as soon as it receives a final score summary from its data providers. {{brandName}} will apply its own verification of these results, and once satisfied will consider a contest final and prizes allocated.</p> <p>Should {{brandName}} consider any results invalid, it will investigate in full prior to considering a contest final.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> What happens if any contests are subject to cancelled games? </accordion-heading> <p>In these situations {{brandName}} will consider any contests involving these games to be invalid and therefore unable to be considered for inclusion in that contest.</p> <p>If this is the case, all participants in such contests will be refunded their entry fee in full.</p> </accordion-group> </accordion> <h2>Deposits and Withdrawals</h2> <accordion> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> Why has my bank charged me a cash advance fee? </accordion-heading> <p>It has come to our attention that some of our customers have been affected by a change of policy regarding credit card deposits. Traditionally, depositing with a credit card was treated as a normal payment by banks and no extra fees were charged to your account. However in recent times it appears that some banks have started charging a surcharge because all deposits into {{siteUri}} are being treated as cash substitutes.</p> <p>To establish whether these surcharges apply to you, you are urged to check with your financial institution for advice on what financial products and services are affected.</p> <p>We would like you to know that {{siteUri}} does not charge any transaction fees to its customers. All the deposit methods listed on our website are paid by us to ensure the amount you want to deposit is what you receive in your balance.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> How can I avoid this fee? </accordion-heading> <p>By using your Debit Card to deposit you will avoid paying a cash advance fee.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> How do I deposit money? </accordion-heading> <p>There are two ways you can deposit money into your {{brandName}} wallet.</p> <p>You can deposit funds by (1) credit card (2) debit card.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> How do I withdraw money? </accordion-heading> <p>You can withdraw your money at anytime. When you choose to withdraw your funds {{brandName}} will deposit the withdrawn amount directly to your nominated bank account.</p> <p>This is subject to both verification of credit cards used for deposit and bank accounts used for withdrawals.</p> <p>Prior to processing all withdrawals {{brandName}} will conduct anti-fraud checks on playing patterns. {{brandName}} may ask you to provide additional information before your withdrawal is approved. If a withdrawal does not meet {{brandName}} terms of use, it reserves the right to refuse the withdrawal request until further investigation.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> I am having difficulties depositing money into my {{brandName}} wallet, what can I do? </accordion-heading> <p>If you are having difficulties depositing money into your {{brandName}} wallet please email us at <a href="mailto:{{supportEmail}}">{{supportEmail}}</a></p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> Why cant I deposit funds? </accordion-heading> <p>{{brandName}} protects its members by limiting the amount of money you can deposit over fixed periods of time. It also limits deposits based on the verification status of a member and their credit cards until such time that verification has been authorized.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> Why cant I withdraw funds? </accordion-heading> <p>{{brandName}} requires all bank accounts used for withdrawals to be be verified. This can be done via your verification status section of <a ui-sref="account.details">my details</a>. Withdrawals are also restricted until such time you have verified all credit cards used for deposits. </p> <p>{{brandName}} also applies limits of withdrawals over periods of time, to ensure safety for our members.</p> </accordion-group> </accordion> <h2>Gameplay and Opponents</h2> <accordion> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> Who do I play against? </accordion-heading> <p>You can (1) pick an opponent or opponents from the <a ui-sref="lobby">lobby page</a>, or (2) challenge your friends via email, Facebook or Twitter.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> How can I challenge my friends? </accordion-heading> <p>Once a new contest is entered and youve picked your line-up, you can challenge friends via email, Facebook or Twitter.</p> <p>If you invite numerous friends to play, the first friend to submit their team will be your opponent.</p> <p>If none of your friends accept your challenge, {{brandName}} will automatically match you to another member.</p> <p>So your friends have time to accept your challenge remember to uncheck the Public Entry box on the line-up selection screen. This keeps your contest from appearing as a public entry.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> What happens if my entry does not get matched or not all the spots are filled in a multi-person game? </accordion-heading> <p>Before the start of a contest, {{siteUri}} run all head to head entries through a matching process this results in most entries being matched up. Once contests of 3 or more players reach 50% filled the contest will run. Any contests which does not reach 50% filled will not run and entry fees will be refunded. One exception to this is guaranteed tournaments. They will run regardless of how many members enter.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> What happens if I enter a contest that does not get filled? </accordion-heading> <p>Multi-person leagues will proceed if entries reach 50% of the contest size. The total prize pool will adjust as per the number of actual entries in the contest. The number of prize winners and the percentage of the prize pool allocated to each winner will remain the same. One exception to this is large tournaments. Prize pool and contest are usually guaranteed for large tournaments regardless of how many members enter.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> Are we allowed to change our line-up once we have entered a contest? </accordion-heading> <p>Line-ups can be edited as many times as you want until the start of a contest. You can view your contest line-ups in the <a ui-sref="upcoming">Upcoming</a> tab in the navigation menu. Once a contest start your selections will be locked in and cannot be edited and your opponents line-up will now be visible.</p> </accordion-group> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> Why can\'t I see all the players who are playing today? </accordion-heading> <p>All sports will display players who are on the team roster for the selected games. To avoid giving late entrants an unfair advantage the players available, their pricing and their positions will not be changed once a contest is created. All {{brandName}} contests are also created up to one week in advance.</p> </accordion-group> </accordion> <h2>Self-Exclusion</h2> <accordion> <accordion-group> <accordion-heading> Can I self-exclude myself from {{brandName}}? </accordion-heading> <p>{{brandName}} encourages customers to take responsibility for their wagering activities. Members can request self-exclusion from all wagering activity by contacting <a href="mailto:{{supportEmail}}?Subject=Self Exclusion Request">{{supportEmail}}</a> with their account details and period of Self-Exclusion. Once the request is verified, the account will be blocked from accessing the {{siteUri}} website.</p> <p>Any requests to cancel a self-exclusion within 7 days will be declined. {{brandName}} reserves the right to extend any exclusion period.</p> </accordion-group> </accordion> </div> </div> </div>'),a.put("views/history.html",'<div class="title-bar"> <div class="container"> <h1 class="title">History</h1> </div> </div> <div class="container" data-ng-controller="HistoryCtrl as ctrl" data-ng-init="ctrl.loadNext()"> <div class="panel panel-default"> <div class="csvDownloadHistory" data-ng-show="ctrl.csvDownloadEnabled"> <i class="fa fa-download"></i> <a href="javascript:void(0);" ng-click="ctrl.exportToCsv()">Download as CSV</a> </div> <div class="panel-body history-scroll-table"> <table class="table table-hover"> <thead> <tr> <th>Contest <th>Date <th>Entry <th>Place <th>Prize <th class="hidden-xs hidden-sm">Type <th class="hidden-xs hidden-sm">Opponents <th class="hidden-xs hidden-sm">ID   <tbody data-infinite-scroll="ctrl.loadNext()" data-infinite-scroll-disabled="ctrl.loadingData || ctrl.loadingDisabled" data-infinite-scroll-distance="0" data-infinite-scroll-immediate-check="false" data-on-vertical-scroll-enabled="ctrl.screenFilled = true" data-on-vertical-scroll-enabled-container="body" data-on-vertical-scroll-enabled-content="div.page > div.main" data-on-vertical-scroll-enabled-offset="400"> <tr ng-repeat="entry in ctrl.contests" data-toggle="collapse" class="accordion-toggle"> <td class="title"> <div class="row"> <div class="sport hidden-xs hidden-sm col-md-2"><i class="mb-icon mb-icon-sport-{{::entry.contest.sport | lowercase | cutWhiteSpace}}"></i></div> <div class="col-md-10"> <a ui-sref="results({contestId: entry.contest.id})"><strong>{{::entry.contest.name}}</strong></a> <br> <small><i>{{ ::entry.contest.contestType }}</i></small> </div> </div>  <td class="prize-pool"><span class="amount">{{$root.formatDate(entry.contest.start, \'MMM Do YYYY - h:mma z\')}}</span> <td class="entry-fee"><span class="amount">{{::entry.contest.entryFee.amount | mbCurrency}}</span> <td class="prize-pool"><span class="amount">{{::entry.place + 1}}</span> <td class="prize-pool"><span class="amount">{{::entry.prize.amount | money: entry.prize.currency}}</span> <td class="hidden-xs hidden-sm"><span class="amount">{{::entry.contest.dateName}}</span> <td class="hidden-xs hidden-sm"><span class="amount">{{::entry.contest.opponentType}}</span> <td class="hidden-xs hidden-sm contestId">{{entry.contest.id | cut:false:8:\' \'}}   </table> <div class="static-info" data-ng-show="ctrl.loadingData"><i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin"></i> Loading...</div> <div class="static-info" ng-if="ctrl.initalLoadComplete &amp;&amp; !ctrl.contests.length" class="text-center">No historical contests</div> </div> </div> </div>'),a.put("views/home.html",'<div class="top"> <div class="already-member"> <a ui-sref="signin" class="btn btn-member">Already a member ?</a> </div> <div class="container"> <div class="logo"></div> <h1>Win <strong>Real</strong> Money Playing <strong>Fantasy</strong> Sports</h1> <h2>With Australia\'s favourite daily &amp; weekly fantasy sports destination</h2> <div class="play"><a ng-click="openVideoModal()"><i class="fa fa-play"></i></a></div> </div> <div class="join"> <div class="container"> <a ui-sref="lobby" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Get Started</a> <p>Its Free to join! Start playing for real money now!</p> </div> </div> </div> <div class="middle"> <div class="container"> <h1>Be part of the Australian revolution in fantasy sports</h1> <div class="wrap"> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm-6"> <ul> <li><i class="mb-icon mb-icon-cash"></i>Real cash prizes</li> <li><i class="mb-icon mb-icon-user"></i>Play your mates and other fans</li> <li><i class="mb-icon mb-icon-calendar"></i>No season long commitment</li> </ul> </div> <div class="col-sm-6"> <ul> <li><i class="mb-icon mb-icon-coins"></i>Entries starting from $2</li> <li><i class="mb-icon mb-icon-group"></i>Contests for 2 to 1000\'s of players</li> <li><i class="mb-icon mb-icon-add"></i>Create your own contests with mates</li> </ul> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <script type="text/ng-template" id="videoModal.html"><div class="modal-header">\n    <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm close" ng-click="$dismiss()" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true"><i class="fa fa-2x fa-times"></i></span></button>\n  </div>\n  <div class="modal-body text-cente